http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Fillip-to-AP-TS-watershed-management-efforts/article14013760.ece

The governments of Telangana and Andhra Pradesh received a major fillip in their efforts for improving watershed management in the rural and rain fed areas.The Central government has signed an agreement with the World Bank for the Neeranchal National Watershed project building up on the longstanding partnership between the two in the watershed management sector.The project envisages a credit of $ 178.5 million for the project launched under the Pradhan Mantri Krishi Sinchayee Yojana (PMKSY) to achieve convergence of investments in irrigation at the field level.Centre signs an agreement with the World Bank for Neeranchal National Watershed project